"United States","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1886,"children_ids":["H03880","H03881","H03882","H03883","H03884"]}],"tags":["new_york_migration"],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909","page":"Entry 2424"}],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[],"cross_connections":[{"related_person_id":"HD3260","relationship":"first_cousin_cousin_marriage_convergence","evidence":"Thomas Edwin's father Thomas Gould (H01270) and Laura's father Myron (H01272) were half-brothers via Capt. Thomas Hooker (H00491) by different mothers. Two of Thomas Edwin's sons each married a Shader-line descendant of Laura: Thomas Harvey (H03872) m. Laura's daughter Caroline E. Shader (X02269); William Henry (H03880) m. Laura's granddaughter Lydia M. Robinson. Two cousin marriages closed the loop between the Thomas Gould and Myron lines.","display_label":"Their children's marriages closed two Hooker-cousin loops","type":"family_connection"},{"type":"cousin_marriage","related_id":"HD3260","display_label":"Her daughter Caroline Shader married his son Thomas Harvey Hooker","notes":"Cousin marriage documentation. H02424 (Thomas Edwin Hooker) and HD3260 (Laura Electa Hooker Shader) are uncle and niece — Laura's father Myron Hooker (H01272) was Thomas Edwin's half-brother. Their respective children H03872 Thomas Harvey Hooker (Thomas Edwin's son) and X02269 Caroline E. Shader (Laura's daughter) were third cousins who married Feb 12, 1863. Children of that marriage (H05030 Lucy and H05031 Alvah) inherit double-Hooker ancestry with descent_paths_to_thomas=2."}],"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM514","plot_notes":"Sandy Creek Cemetery Murray Orleans County New York per FA"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"thomas-hooker-1813"},"H03880":{"id":"H03880","former_ids":["HD3231"],"is_placeholder":false,"gender":"male","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":9,"is_easter_egg":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true},"bio":{"first_name":"William","middle_name":"Henry","last_name":"Hooker","married_names":[],"gender":"male","display_name":"William Henry Hooker","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1777229610/williamhenryhooker1864_gn3m0w.png","photo_notes":"Findagrave-sourced photo via Cloudinary"},"birth":{"year":1864,"month":8,"day":18,"city":"Murray","county":"Orleans County","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1933,"month":5,"day":15,"city":"Brockport","county":"Monroe County","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"parents":{"father_id":"H02424","mother_id":"X02242"},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"HD3270","date_year":1890,"location_country":"United States","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1915,"children_ids":["HD3236","HD3237","HD3238"]}],"tags":["cousin_marriage","new_york_migration"],"sources":[{"short":"Findagrave"}],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Married fellow Hooker descendant, third-cousin distance","body":"William Henry 'Willie' Hooker married Lydia Mason Robinson — herself a Hooker descendant via her grandmother Laura E. Hooker Shader, daughter of Captain Thomas Hooker's son Myron Hooker. William Henry and Lydia were third cousins once removed; their marriage united two Hooker-line branches in a single household, with their son Charles Theodore Hooker holding documented double Hooker ancestry through both parents."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Two brothers each married a Shader-line Hooker cousin","body":"The cousin marriage was paralleled in the family: William Henry's brother Thomas Harvey Hooker had also married a Shader-line Hooker cousin (Caroline E. Shader, Lydia's aunt). Two brothers Thomas Edwin Hooker's sons each thus married a Shader-line Hooker woman, making their offspring doubly Hooker-descended on both maternal and paternal sides. The pattern thickened the Hooker-line concentration in the Murray, Orleans County New York branch."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Born Murray NY 1864, three children with Lydia","body":"William Henry Hooker was born August 18, 1864 in Murray, Orleans County New York — the eldest child of Thomas Edwin Hooker by his second wife Susan M. Brown. He died May 15, 1933 in Brockport, Monroe County New York at age sixty-eight, buried at Beach Ridge Cemetery Brockport. He had three children with Lydia: C. Theodore Hooker (1891-1971), Ethel Susan Hooker Zastrow (1896-1928 died young at 31), and Marjory Violetta Hooker Delahanty (1902-1993)."}],"cross_connections":[],"burial":{"plot_notes":"Beach Ridge Cemetery, Brockport, Monroe County NY (per Findagrave). Same as wife Lydia Mason Robinson Hooker."},"nickname":"Willie","residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"william-hooker-1864"},"HD3270":{"id":"HD3270","former_ids":["X02243"],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":true,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"is_easter_egg":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":10,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true},"bio":{"first_name":"Lydia","middle_name":"Mason","last_name":"Hooker","maiden_name":"Robinson","married_names":["Hooker"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Lydia Mason Robinson Hooker"},"birth":{"year":1865,"month":7,"day":9,"state":"New York","country":"United States","city":"Murray","county":"Orleans County"},"death":{"year":1915,"month":2,"day":8,"city":"Holley","county":"Orleans County","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"parents":{"father_id":"X02287","mother_id":"HD3269"},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"H03880","date_year":1889,"date_month":1,"date_day":19,"location_state":"New York","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1915,"children_ids":["HD3236","HD3237","HD3238"]}],"tags":["cousin_marriage"],"sources":[{"short":"EH 3880 (as William Henry Hooker spouse)"},{"short":"WikiTree + Findagrave"}],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Cousin marriage united two Hooker-line branches","body":"Lydia Mason Robinson married William Henry Hooker on January 19, 1889 — the marriage joining two Hooker-line branches in a single household. Lydia descended from Captain Thomas Hooker through her grandmother Laura Electa Hooker Shader (Myron Hooker's daughter); William Henry descended through the parallel Thomas Edwin Hooker branch. They were third cousins once removed, and their three children inherited double Hooker ancestry."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Three children, daughter Ethel died age thirty-one","body":"Lydia and William Henry had three children: Charles Theodore Hooker (1891-1971), Ethel Susan Hooker Zastrow (1896-1928 died young at thirty-one), and Marjory Violetta Hooker Delahanty (1902-1993). The Hooker-Zastrow line traces forward through Ethel; the Hebner-Cook-Stafford family that descended from these children is doubly Hooker-descended on both maternal and paternal sides."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Born Murray NY 1865, died Holley 1915","body":"Lydia Mason Robinson was born July 9 or 10, 1865 in Murray, Orleans County New York. She died February 8, 1915 in Holley, Orleans County New York at age forty-nine — predeceasing her husband William Henry by eighteen years. The Orleans County NY core of the Hooker-Shader-Robinson cousin network spanned three generations of intermarriages within the same upstate New York county."}],"cross_connections":[],"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"lydia-hooker-1865"},"HD3236":{"id":"HD3236","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"gender":"male","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":10,"is_easter_egg":false,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true},"bio":{"first_name":"C","middle_name":"Theodore","last_name":"Hooker","married_names":[],"gender":"male","display_name":"C Theodore Hooker"},"birth":{"year":1891,"month":8,"day":24,"county":"Orleans County","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1971,"month":8,"county":"Monroe County","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"parents":{"father_id":"H03880","mother_id":"HD3270"},"marriages":[],"tags":["double_hooker_ancestry","western_new_york_migration"],"sources":[{"short":"Findagrave"}],"burial":{"plot_notes":"Beach Ridge Cemetery, Brockport, Monroe County NY (per Findagrave). GPS 43.1907564 -77.9415601."},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"narrative_blocks":[],"cross_connections":[],"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"c-hooker-1891"},"HD3237":{"id":"HD3237","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"gender":"female","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":10,"is_easter_egg":false,"include_in_path_calculation":tr